history.content: You shouldn't have been in 999; the section had 0 seats allocated to it. I have no idea what would happen if you stayed, but I would imagine that you wouldn't actually be enrolled properly.

children.subject: I've been enrolled in the 999 section for CS188. I did not get an email to drop the course and re-enroll, so am I fine staying in section 999? It doesn't seem like a good idea for me to drop and re-enroll at this point.

history.content: I attempted to enroll in CS 188 and got into DIS 999 like everyone else in this Piazza, but based on the misleading email and an advisor's recommendation to check @5203 I assumed that my only option to get into the class was to drop DIS 999 and attempt to enroll in another section.  When I dropped DIS 999, I couldn't get into another discussion.  All of these posts are confusing and seem to conflict -- if I got into DIS 999 and got the email, am I in the class or not?  And, was dropping 999 the right option, or should I have stuck with my position in 999?  Most importantly, is there any chance whatsoever of me getting into CS 188 now that I've been thoroughly misled and confused or should I give up and try for other classes?
